  "commentary": "With SPX at 6562.08 trading below the 6570 GEX flip in a PIN regime, dealers are positioned to buy this dip as they're long gamma and providing stabilizing flow. The massive positive gamma wall at 6580 (+26.2B) will create significant selling pressure if we rally there, while the thick cluster of positive GEX from 6565-6580 suggests we're entering a consolidation zone with mean-reverting behavior expected.\n\nWatch for dealer buying support to kick in here given we're below the flip, but any move toward 6580 will face heavy dealer selling as they hedge their long gamma positions - that level is your key resistance to fade rallies against.",
